This paper deals with the problem of human pose estimation and tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses a flow-based pose tracker, which involves the use of optical flow, a technique commonly used in robotics and control systems, hence cs.RO (Robotics) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also uses deep learning models, which is a common technique in multimedia analysis, hence cs.MM (Multimedia) is another likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of object detection and tracking, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence, hence cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of extensive experiments to validate various choices of models and configurations, which is a common technique in machine learning, hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category.
